Craig Brewer, Co-head for Banking at ABSA, explains the possible implications for the South African gold sector following recent mergers and challenges that lie ahead for investment in the sector. WATCH THE VIDEO TO HEAR HIS INSIGHTS THAT MAY AFFECT YOUR BUSINESS Another key focus on the gold sector is the nearly four-month-long strike at Sibanye-Stillwater’s gold division has resulted in gold production in December plunging to its worst level since October 2012. Data from StatsSA indicated that gold output tanked by 31% y-o-y in December 2018.   